One \
\uc0\u8232 The Tao that can be told is not the eternal Tao. \u8232 The name that can be named is not the eternal name. \u8232 The nameless is the beginning of heaven and Earth. \u8232 The named is the mother of the ten thousand things. \u8232 Ever desireless, one can see the mystery. \u8232 Ever desiring, one sees the manifestations. \u8232 These two spring from the same source but differ in name; this appears as darkness. \u8232 Darkness within darkness. \u8232 The gate to all mystery.\
